verbose_text: MAP4K5 (MIM : 604923)--also known as germinal center kinase related (GCKR)--at chromosome 14q22.1 (rs1032466, OR = 0.82, p meta = 1.96 x 10 -17) has been shown to be activated by both TNF and WNT3A, and decreased expression of MAP4K5 inhibits GSK3beta phosphorylation and subsequent beta-catenin accumulation in B lymphocytes.
